text:
State Budget 2020: What revenues and expenses increased by the second reading

05 Nov 2019, 18:10


Today, the Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine presented the draft Law “On the State Budget of Ukraine for 2020”, finalized for second reading.

This was reported by the press service of the Ministry of Finance.
According to the report, it was proposed to increase state budget revenues (without transfers) by UAH 14.18 billion for 2020, including UAH 11.9 billion for the general fund and UAH 2.3 billion for the special fund. The deficit will amount to 2.09% of GDP. The costs of the revised draft budget increased to 1,180.1 billion UAH.
It is noted that the document is balanced and aimed at resolving pressing issues and implementing the Program of Activities of the Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine. First of all, spending on solving pressing issues of both a social and economic nature will increase.
In particular, revenues and expenses were increased by:
- providing schools with necessary equipment - 3.5 billion UAH;
- improvement of social protection of certain categories of teachers of general secondary education institutions provides for a subvention of 3.8 billion UAH;
- The creation of training centers of modern professional education increased by 159 million UAH;
- assistance to families with children - UAH 2.2 billion;
- design, construction and repair work, the purchase of housing and premises for the development of family forms of education and housing for orphans - by 364.1 million UAH;
- assistance to single pensioners - by 860 million UAH;
- centralized purchase of medicines and medical products for the treatment of certain diseases - 3.2 billion UAH;
- modernization and updating of the material and technical base of multidisciplinary intensive care hospitals - 1 billion UAH;
- treatment of Ukrainian citizens abroad - for 400 million UAH;
- implementation of measures of socio-economic development of territories - 2 billion UAH;
- construction, reconstruction, repair and maintenance of public roads of local importance, streets and roads of communal ownership in settlements - by 1.5 million UAH.
- construction and reconstruction of bridges - for 500 million UAH;
- land inventory and updating the cartographic basis of the State Land Cadastre - by 291.9 million UAH;
- the withdrawal of state coal mining enterprises to the break-even level - by 622.8 million UAH;
- the program "Country stapling - youth mobility project" - 500 million UAH;
- for the creation of the Museum of Modern Art of Ukraine - 54 million UAH;
- International Children's Center "Artek" - for 9.8 million UAH.
The costs of national security and defense amount to UAH 245.8 billion, in particular, for:
- cash collateral and wages (with accruals) - 141.4 billion UAH (+ 14.4 billion UAH by 2019);
- medicines and dressings - 657.8 million UAH (+ 82.8 million UAH by 2019);
- food products - 4.84 billion UAH (+ 248.1 million UAH by 2019);
- payment of utilities and energy - 4.9 billion UAH (+ 510.7 million UAH by 2019);
- the creation, purchase, modernization and repair of weapons and military (special) equipment - 35.4 billion UAH (+ 7.8 billion UAH by 2019);
- Payment of one-time cash assistance in the event of death (death), disability or partial disability and other social payments - 6.66 billion UAH (+ 2.44 billion UAH by 2019);
- construction (acquisition) of housing - UAH 2.23 billion (+389.8 million UAH by 2019).
In addition, it is noted that the volume of public debt in hryvnia equivalent will amount to UAH 2,045.1 billion and will amount to 45.3% of forecast GDP. The volume of payments on the repayment of public debt for 2020 is projected in the amount of UAH 282.1 billion, including the repayment of state external debt - UAH 120.3 billion, and state internal debt - 161.9 billion UAH. For payments on servicing the public debt for 2020, 141.5 billion UAH is provided. Proceeds from privatization increased by UAH 7 billion, which will reduce the volume of planned borrowing.
Recall that Alexey Goncharuk said that in the budget for 2020 the government is not looking for additional resources to raise taxes, but offers to reduce administrative costs and services for the government and central executive bodies by an average of 10%.
Goncharuk also called the new figures of the state budget for 2020.

